ELIZABETH N. DEAN, Plaintiff and Appellant, v. THE N. Y. CENTRAL AND HUDSON R. R. R. COMPANY, Defendant and Respondent. Decided June 25, 1877.

Before Sedowick, Speir and Freedman, JJ.

Appeal from judgment for defendant on report of referee. Robert I. Little, for appellant. Frank Loomis, for respondent.

The only question involved was whether the evidence was supported by the referee’s findings of fact.

Per Curiam.

—Judgment affirmed with costs.
